{
  "name": "Instant Summons",
  "_id": "matSplInstantSum",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You touch the gemstoneused in the casting and an object weighing 10 pounds or less whose longest dimension is 6 feet or less. The spell leaves an Invisible mark on that object and invisibly inscribes the object's name on the gemstone. Each time you cast this spell, you must use a different gemstone.</p><p>Thereafter, you can take a Magic action to speak the object's name and crush the gemstone. The object instantly appears in your hand regardless of physical or planar distances, and the spell ends.</p><p>If another creature is holding or carrying the object, crushing the gemstone doesn't transport it, but instead you learn who that creature is and where that creature is currently located.</p><section class=\"secret\" id=\"secret-px4JJQv7QxLmPdka\"><p><strong>Foundry Note</strong></p><p>This spell's Limited Uses are configured to track the number of inscribed objects, with the \"Inscribe\" and \"Recall\" activities restoring and consuming uses as appropriate.</p></section>",
